{"lemma": "شَجَّةٌ", "slug": "شَجَّةٌ", "root": "ش.ج.ج", "root_slug": "ش-ج-ج", "root_link": "/words/roots/ش-ج-ج", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": false}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n21707"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8E%D8%AC%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "head wound", "fa": "زخم سر", "ur": "سر کی چوٹ", "tr": "kafa yarası", "id": "luka kepala", "bn": "মাথার আঘাত", "es": "herida en la cabeza", "fr": "blessure à la tête", "de": "Kopfverletzung", "ru": "рана головы", "zh": "头部伤口"}, "definition": null, "etymology": null, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n21707", "headword_ar": "شَجَّةٌ", "root": "$j", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A single act of breaking"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of one's head ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "so as to cleave its skin"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "its flesh"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A wound by which the head is broken"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, * A, * L, Msb)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "so as to cleave its skin"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "its flesh:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L:) and ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "such"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a wound in the face:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, * Msb:) pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$ijaAjN", "text_ar": "شِجَاجٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, A, L, Msb) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$aj~aAtN", "text_ar": "شَجَّاتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Msb.) What are termed"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$ijaAj", "text_ar": "شِجَاج"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "are of ten different kinds, (A, L,) distinguished by the following epithets: [1]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaAriSapN", "text_ar": "حَارِصَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which peels off the [external] skin, but does not bring blood: [2]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daAmiyapN", "text_ar": "دَامِيَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which brings blood: [3]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baADiEapN", "text_ar": "بَاضِعَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [which cleaves the flesh slightly, and brings blood, but does not make it to flow: (but in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dmg", "text_ar": "دمغ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daAmigapN", "text_ar": "دَامِغَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", q. v., what are here mentioned as the second and third are transposed:) 4,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mutalaAHimapN", "text_ar": "مُتَلَاحِمَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",] which cleaves the flesh much: [5]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "simoHaAqN", "text_ar": "سِمْحَاقٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which leaves between it and the bone only a thin skin: these are five"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$jAj", "text_ar": "شجاج"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for which there is no retaliation nor any determinate mulct, but respecting which a judge must give his sentence: [6]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "muwDiHapN", "text_ar": "مُوضِحَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which reaches to the bone, and for which the mulct is five camels: [7]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "haA$imapN", "text_ar": "هَاشِمَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which breaks the bone, and for which the mulct is ten camels: [8]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "munaq~ilapN", "text_ar": "مُنَقِّلَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", from which bone is removed, from one place to another, and for which the mulct is fifteen camels: [9]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA^omuwmapN", "text_ar": "مَاْمُومَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", also called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A=m~apN", "text_ar": "ا=مَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which leaves between it and the brain only a thin skin, and for which the mulct is one third of the whole price of blood: [10]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daAmigapN", "text_ar": "دَامِغَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which reaches the brain, and for which the mulct is also one third of the whole price of blood. (L.) The"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$aj~ap", "text_ar": "شَجَّة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of 'Abd-El-Hameed, [who was the goodliest man of his age,] the son of 'Abd-Allah the son of 'Omar the son of El-Khattáb, was the subject of a prov. on account of its beauty [and is said to have increased his goodliness]. (MF.)"}], "source_refs": ["L", "S", "A", "Msb"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}